.\" Hsh Simple Shell manpage - Holberton School
.TH HSH_Simple_SHell 1 "19 November 2019" "v0.1.0" "SIMPLE SHELL PROYECT"
.SH NAME
hsh - GNU Holberton-SHell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "headers.h"
.br
.SH FILES
.B AUTHORS
.br
.B headers.h
.br
.B README.md
.br
.B shell.c
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
simple shell is an input command interpreter that executes specific
instructions in the system.
.B hsh
simple shell parsers
.I external
commands such as
.I ls
,
.I cp
,
.I mv
,
.I cat
,
.I less
, etc. allocated in the
.I /bin
directory. This is a simple version expected to output and execute what
it is asked for.
.SS Arguments
The first argument (position 0) is assumed as a file containing shell
commands. The following arguments and their positional parameters are set
for the remaining arguments. If the file in the current directory is not
found the shell will search
.BR PATH
directories searching for the script.
.SS Exit Status
Once the command is executed the shell will exit status. Exit status occurs
when the shell command finishes the last command inside the script.
.SH Example
An example output produced by the shell is the following:
.TP
.B $ cat AUTHORS
Jaime Andrés Gálvez Villamarin <1167@holbertonschool.com>
.br
Luis Alejandro Herrera Bolaños <1209@holbertonschool.com>
